                  <ab type="history">Dabr. The ṣabal-source (of <persName ref="PRS10581Zamika" type="tabot">ʾAragāwi</persName>?) is located in the vicinity of the church. &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">14 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy001">BGY-001</ref> "Synaxarion (January-June)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy002">BGY-002</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy003">BGY-003</ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy004">BGY-004</ref> "The Book of the Rite of the Passion Week"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy005">BGY-005</ref> "The Miracles of Mary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy006">BGY-006</ref> "Four Gospels"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy007">BGY-007</ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy008">BGY-008</ref> "Synaxarion (the first half of the year)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy009">BGY-009</ref> "Antiphonary"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy010">BGY-010</ref> "Synaxarion (second half of the year)"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy011">BGY-011</ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy012">BGY-012</ref> "Text devoted to John the Baptist"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy013">BGY-013</ref> "The Homily of St. Michael"; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbgy014">BGY-014</ref> "The Loosening of the Spell"</ab>
              
